</div>
<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><strong>Darlington Chibueze Anuonye</strong> is editor of <em>The Good Teacher: An Anthology of Essays in Honour of Teachers</em> as well as curator of <em>Selfies and Signatures: An Afro Anthology of Short Stories</em> and <em>Through the Eye of a Needle: Art in the Time of Coronavirus</em>. He is also co-editor of <em>Daybreak: An Anthology of Nigerian Short Fiction</em>. Anuonye was awarded the 2021 Amplify Fellowship of the MasterCard Foundation and longlisted for the 2018 Babishai Niwe African Poetry Award.</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
